I investigated the source code of Java MySQL JDBC.

There are two types, one is the MySQL Type, another one is the JDBC type.
MySQL Type means how MySQL store the data.
JDBC type means how JDBC process the data.

MySQL type `BINARY` will be mapped to JDBC type `CHAR`, but this is a special type of string. Which should encode and decode by the users. [MySQL Docs](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.6/en/binary-varbinary.html)

