That means Sharding-Proxy think this is `CHAR`, so send the data as String to user.
Actually this is a byte array in JDBC.

What's more, Sharding-Proxy shouldn't try to convert JDBC type to MySQL type.
For example, in JDBC source code, both `MysqlDefs.FIELD_TYPE_JSON` and `MysqlDefs.FIELD_TYPE_STRING` will convert to `Types.CHAR`.

If Sharding-Proxy try to do that, the user will receive the wrong MySQL type.

